The paper discusses the role of commitments in human-robot interaction, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the cognitive and behavioral aspects of commitments, which suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper explores the use of commitments in guiding robots, which is a topic related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents a framework for exploring the capacities and behaviors needed for commitment management, which could fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.MA).
